OL,4,CFather and son guilty of #1.7m antiques
OL,5,Ctheft from Bedford widow
OL,6, A father and son have been found guilty
OL,7, of stealing antiques worth about #1.7m
OL,8, from a wealthy widow.
OL,10,FDes, 83, and Gary Pickersgill, 42, sold
OL,11,Fitems including Chinese jade and ivory
OL,12,Fornaments, taken from the 96-year-old
OL,13,Fwoman's home near Bedford.
OL,15,FLuton Crown Court heard they were taken
OL,16,Ffrom an unlocked cabinet between
OL,17,FNovember 2011 and May 2018.
OL,19,FDes Pickersgill said the items had been
OL,20,Fgiven to him, but the pair were found
OL,21,Fguilty of theft on Monday.
